Selection Sort
Selection Sort is a simple comparison-based sorting algorithm that repeatedly finds the smallest element from the unsorted part of the array and places it at the beginning.
The array is divided into two parts: sorted and unsorted. In each iteration, the minimum element from the unsorted section is selected and swapped with the first unsortedelement
Time Complexity

Best Case: O(n²)

Average Case: O(n²)

Worst Case: O(n²)

Space Complexity

O(1) (in-place sorting)


class SelectionSort {
    static void selectionSort(int arr[]) {
        int n = arr.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            int minIndex = i;

            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (arr[j] < arr[minIndex]) {
                    minIndex = j;
                }
            }

            int temp = arr[minIndex];
            arr[minIndex] = arr[i];
            arr[i] = temp;
        }
    }
}
